[2] South Korea: imported
Date: Wed 22 Jun 2022
Source: South Korea News Net [edited]
https://www.southkoreanews.net/news/272594399/1st-ld-writethru-s-korea-confirms-1st-monkeypox-infection


South Korea confirmed its first case of monkeypox infection on Wednesday [22 Jun 2022] out of 2 suspected cases. A South Korean national who arrived here from Germany on Tuesday afternoon [21 Jun 2022] was confirmed to be infected with the virus, according to the Korea Disease Control and Prevention Agency (KDCA).

The patient developed headache on Saturday [18 Jun 2022] and showed symptoms, including mild fever, sore throat, asthenia, fatigue and skin lesions, on arrival. The South Korean voluntarily reported to the health authorities and was admitted to the Incheon Medical Center in Incheon, west of the capital Seoul.

Another suspected patient, a foreigner who arrived here on Monday [20 Jun 2022], tested positive for chickenpox, not monkeypox. After developing a sore throat and skin lesions from Sunday [19 Jun 2022], the foreigner visited a hospital in Busan, about 450 km south east of Seoul, on Tuesday [21 Jun 2022] and was admitted to the hospital for treatment.

The health authorities raised the risk level of monkeypox from "attention" to "caution" to contain the virus spread through cooperation among ministries. South Korea has designated monkeypox as a 2nd-degree infectious disease in its 4-tier system. In the 2nd-degree category are 22 contagious diseases, including COVID-19.

