[5] Chile: imported
Date: Tue 21 Jun 2022
Source: eju [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, abridged, edited]
https://eju.tv/2022/06/chile-confirma-un-segundo-caso-de-viruela-del-mono/


Chile added its 2nd case of monkeypox on Monday [20 Jun 2022] in a person who traveled to Europe, 3 days after the 1st infection was confirmed, according to the Ministry of Health. The virus was detected through PCR analysis in an adult person from the La Araucan√≠a region, 600 kilometers [373 mi] south of Santiago, who had traveled to Europe in the last 3 weeks.

As with the first registered case, "the person is in good health, without complications and is serving a period of isolation," officials reported from the ministry.

Last Friday [17 Jun 2022], the infection of a young adult from the Metropolitan Region, in which the capital is located, was confirmed. The case also had a history of a trip to Europe and presented with spots and scabs on the skin.

